---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Reach" description="Directions to Tamarind Valley Collective from the Tamil Nadu and Karnataka sides, plus a bit of history about the surrounding forest." image="/images/pages/how-to-reach/hero.png" imageWidth={1112} imageHeight={428}>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Visit TVC" title="How to Reach" image="/images/pages/how-to-reach/hero.png" imageAlt="Map directions to the farm" />

  <section class="section wrapper">
    <p>Search for "The Tamarind Collective" on Google Maps to get directions. The farm can be reached from the Tamil Nadu side (via Tenkannikottai or Thally) or from the Karnataka side (via Hunasanahalli).</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Coming from east of the Silk Board–Hosur highway (Whitefield, Outer Ring Road, HSR Layout, etc.) — use the Tamil Nadu side route.</li>
      <li>Coming from west of the Silk Board–Hosur highway (Jayanagar, JP Nagar, Bannerghatta Road) — use the Karnataka side route.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Tip:</strong> load the driving directions while you have WiFi so the route buffers — cell reception near the farm is poor across all providers.</p>

    <h3>Karnataka side directions</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>At Kanakapura, take a sharp left turn towards Kodihalli.</li>
      <li>After about 5–6 km, take another quick left (you'll cross the Arkavathi River).</li>
      <li>Take another left once you reach Kodihalli.</li>
      <li>Take a left again before reaching Thaggatti village — look for the BSNL phone tower; the turn is a narrow cement bund after the primary school, next to the hand pump.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Location</h3>
    <p>The farm is in the village of Thaggatti in Tamil Nadu, about 7 km from Hunsanahalli, the border town in Karnataka, and adjacent to the Thaggatti Reserve Forest.</p>
    <p>The area's history is documented by renowned hunter-turned-conservationist <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenneth_Anderson_(writer)#Jungle_folk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kenneth Anderson</a>, in his story "Man-eater of Jowlagiri" — the places he mentions are well documented by fans of his writing, and he also references the village of Anchetty in another account, "Sher Khan and the Bettamugalam Man-eater."</p>
    <div class="map-embed">
      <iframe
        loading="lazy"
        src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=The+Tamarind+Collective,+Thaggatti&t=p&z=12&output=embed"
        width="100%"
        height="420"
        style="border:0"
        title="Map showing TVC bordering the Thaggatti Reserve Forest"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
    <p class="caption">TVC bordering the Thaggatti Reserve Forest</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .map-embed {
    margin-top: 20px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  }

  .map-embed iframe {
    display: block;
  }

  .caption {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--tvc-ink-soft);
    margin-top: 10px;
  }
</style>
